ZH: 我买了一台望远镜，可以观察星星。
EN: I bought a telescope to observe stars.

ZH: 他用望远镜观察到了一颗流星。
EN: He spotted a shooting star through the telescope.

ZH: 这台望远镜可以放大物体十倍。
EN: This telescope can magnify objects ten times.

ZH: 我们在山顶上用望远镜观看了美丽的日落。
EN: We watched the beautiful sunset through a telescope from the mountaintop.

ZH: 这款望远镜配备了高清晰度镜片。
EN: This telescope is equipped with high-definition lenses.

ZH: 望远镜的焦距可以调节。
EN: The focal length of the telescope is adjustable.

ZH: 我没有带望远镜去观测太空探索。
EN: I didn't bring a telescope to observe space exploration.

ZH: 他花了很多时间调试望远镜的镜面。
EN: He spent a lot of time adjusting the mirror of the telescope.

ZH: 我利用这台望远镜观察到了一个未知的星系。
EN: With this telescope, I spotted an unknown galaxy.

ZH: 来测量一下望远镜的焦距。
EN: Come and measure the focal length of the telescope.

ZH: 这架望远镜具有自动对焦功能。
EN: This telescope has an automatic focusing function.

ZH: 他通过望远镜看到了一轮明月。
EN: He saw a bright moon through the telescope.

ZH: 我的儿子对望远镜非常感兴趣，总是用它观察天空。
EN: My son is very interested in telescopes and always uses them to observe the sky.

ZH: 望远镜让我们能够更好地研究宇宙。
EN: Telescopes allow us to study the universe better.

ZH: 她通过望远镜观察到了一只高飞的鹰。
EN: She spotted a soaring eagle through the telescope.

ZH: 当你通过望远镜看到行星的轨道，会让你感到惊叹。
EN: It's amazing to see the orbit of a planet through a telescope.

ZH: 这个天文爱好者有一整套的望远镜设备。
EN: This astronomer has a complete set of telescope equipment.

ZH: 他使用一支望远镜寻找银河系中的行星。
EN: He uses a telescope to search for planets in the Milky Way.

ZH: 我的望远镜需要进行清洁，镜片上有灰尘。
EN: My telescope needs to be cleaned as there is dust on the lenses.

ZH: 望远镜打开之后，我们看到了一个宏伟的星系。
EN: After opening the telescope, we saw a magnificent galaxy.
